content: I'm fairly certain that Vue warns against creating components with the same name as native HTML elements, like `header` and `button`, unless you assign them a different id in the `components`property. Maybe it would be better for the sake of the article to rename those element instead. I usually go for something like `UIButton` to make the distinction clear ;) Other than that: a good article that hopefully shines some light on how easy it is to get stuff going with Vue.
